JOHANNESBURG South Africa s top-ranked Kevin Anderson continued his slide in the world ratings as he fell three spots to 79th in ATP singles rankings released on Monday.The strong-serving Anderson achieved a career-high 10th ranking in October 2015.SA s number two singles player, Lloyd Harris also dropped three places to 280th.On the doubles side, Raven Klaasen moved down one place to 13th in the rankings.Chanel Simmonds is the top South African on the women s singles rankings at 331st. Simmonds is also the top women s doubles player at 221st.Men Singles Previous Current 76 79 Kevin Anderson 277 280 Lloyd Harris 512 512 Nik Scholtz 637 637 Tucker Vorster 1,437 1,434 Damon Gooch 1,486 1,482 Joshua Howard-Tripp 1,486 1,482 Bertus Kruger 1,507 1,508 Timothy Dollman 1,544 1,546 Johannes Myburgh 1,654 1,652 Taine Bernhard 1,654 1,652 Philip Henning 1,654 1,652 Sipho Montsi 1,654 1,652 Ruan Roelofse 1,770 1,765 Ruben Alberts Doubles Previous Current 12 13 Raven Klaasen 184 186 Ruan Roelofse 199 201 Dean O Brien 271 277 Tucker Vorster 304 312 Nik Scholtz 784 781 Lloyd Harris 862 861 Keith-Patrick Crowley 905 1,013 Damon Gooch 1,273 1,276 Rikus De Villiers Women Singles Previous Current 329 331 Chanel Simmonds 937 961 Ilze Hattingh 1,055 1,056 Madrie Le Roux Doubles Previous Current 222 221 Chanel Simmonds 666 689 Ilze Hattingh 803 799 Eden D Oliveira 967 966 Madrie Le Roux ITF Junior Boys (as of 20 February 2017) Combined Rankings Previous Current 92 97 Sipho Montsi 99 104 Bertus Kruger 108 112 Richard Thongoana 132 134 Joshua Howard-Tripp 158 162 Philip Henning 210 216 Lleyton Cronje 241 244 Matthew Johnson 277 284 Lance-Pierre Du Toit 328 335 Taine Bernhard 347 355 James Roelofse ITF Junior Girls (as of 20 February 2017) Combined Rankings Previous Current 130 140 Zoe Kruger 202 207 Minette Van Vreden 370 367 Megan Lombardi 378 376 Maxine Bateman 538 536 Margo Landman 401 538 Mila Hartig 639 545 Myah Petchey 588 582 Lee Barnard 645 642 Lara Claudia Van der Merwe ITF Wheel